<div class='function'><span class='function_name'><a class='anchor' id='checkbox.__init__'>checkbox</a>.<b>__init__(form, text='checkbox', frame=False, group=None, checked=False, click_accepts=False, var=None)</b></span><div class='details'>
Constructor<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>form</span> &rarr; the parent form
<br />
<br />
<span class='keyword'>Keyword arguments:</span>
<br />
<span class='variable'>text</span> &rarr; checkbox text (default='checkbox')
<br />
<span class='variable'>frame</span> &rarr; indicates whether a frame should be drawn around the widget
<br />
(default=False)<br />
<span class='variable'>group</span> &rarr; if a group is specified, checking one checkbox from the group
<br />
will uncheck all other checkboxes in that group (default=None)<br />
<span class='variable'>checked</span> &rarr; the checked state of the checkbox (default=False)
<br />
<span class='variable'>click_accepts</span> &rarr; indicates whether a click press should accept and
<br />
close the form (default=False)<br />
<span class='variable'>var</span> &rarr; the name of the experimental variable that should be used to log
<br />
the widget status (default=None)<br />
</div></div>
